# tracker-service — REST Client tests for VS Code
# Install the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client) and click "Send Request" above each block.
# Requests are run sequentially; later requests reference variables captured from earlier responses.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@deviceId = phone-test-001

###  1. Health check
GET {{host}}/health

###  2. Register a new device
# @name register
POST {{host}}/devices/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deviceId": "{{deviceId}}",
  "name": "Test Phone",
  "type": "cyclist"
}

###  3. Capture the API key from the previous response
@apiKey = {{register.response.body.apiKey}}

###  4. Send a GPS ping (Rome, Colosseum)
POST {{host}}/location
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "lat": 41.8902,
  "lng": 12.4922,
  "speed": 5.2
}

###  5. Send another GPS ping (slightly moved)
POST {{host}}/location
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "lat": 41.8903,
  "lng": 12.4925,
  "speed": 5.4
}

###  6. Send a ping with an explicit timestamp
POST {{host}}/location
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "lat": 41.8905,
  "lng": 12.4930,
  "speed": 6.0,
  "timestamp": "2026-05-06T12:00:00.000Z"
}

###  7. Try a ping with a bad API key (should return 401)
POST {{host}}/location
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: not-a-real-key

{
  "lat": 41.8902,
  "lng": 12.4922
}

###  8. Try a ping with no API key (should return 401)
POST {{host}}/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lat": 41.8902,
  "lng": 12.4922
}

###  9. Try a ping with invalid lat (should return 400)
POST {{host}}/location
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "lat": 999,
  "lng": 12.4922
}

### 10. Fetch history for the test device
GET {{host}}/location/{{deviceId}}/history

### 11. Fetch limited history
GET {{host}}/location/{{deviceId}}/history?limit=3

### 12. List all registered devices (no api keys returned)
GET {{host}}/devices

### 13. Re-register the same deviceId (should return existing record, not 500)
POST {{host}}/devices/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deviceId": "{{deviceId}}",
  "name": "Test Phone",
  "type": "cyclist"
}

### 14. Register with invalid type (should return 400)
POST {{host}}/devices/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deviceId": "phone-test-002",
  "name": "Bad Type",
  "type": "spaceship"
}

### 15. Register with missing fields (should return 400)
POST {{host}}/devices/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deviceId": "phone-test-003"
}
